ctm2git
=======

Synthesize a packaging repo from the history of source packages in CTM.

* Run 'ctm2git PACKAGENAME' to create PACKAGENAME.lst
* Edit PACKAGENAME.lst, replacing 'unknown <unknown@unknown.invalid>' with maintainer details for each version
* Run 'ctm2git PACKAGENAME --create' to create git repo in PACAKAGENAME.git/

Note that on the first run this will download all historic setup.ini files from
CTM, which may take a while. These files are cached for subsequent runs.


Advanced usage
--------------

* You can stich together x86 and x86_64 histories by combining their PACKAGENAME.lst files
* If the git repo already exists but is missing recent history, you can use '--since VERSION-RELEASE'
